<subSubSection id="D9BA65676B36FFEAFF00AD88BECA162B" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="911F36EC6B36FFEAFF00AD88BB75165B" blockId="31.[151,1436,426,852]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="A3D4EAFE6B36FFEAFF00AD88BE1C158B" bold="true" box="[151,281,426,452]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species can be identified by its antennae flattened at base, lower anterior angle of lateral lobe of pronotum attenuated and projecting; inner spurs of hind tibia strong, longer than external one and as long as second segment of tarsus; tegmina with brown ferruginous spots, wings transparent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="911F36EC6B36FFEAFF52AE00BECA162B" blockId="31.[151,1436,426,852]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="A3D4EAFE6B36FFEAFF52AE00BE3F1673" bold="true" box="[197,314,546,572]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Habitats:</emphasis>
It lives in amongst grass, usually dry, though one was caught on long grass in water and on old cultivation and vegetation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
